      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. one more thing though—i read somewhere that the tube can get clogged up by tiny things like bugs or ice. how does that actually affect the reading? like if there's a blockage, does the airspeed reading just go to zero or something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
